.SH "NAME"
mutex_lock_interruptible \- acquire the mutex, interruptible
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ __sched\ mutex_lock_interruptible('u
.BI "int __sched mutex_lock_interruptible(struct\ mutex\ *\ " "lock" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIlock\fR
.RS 4
the mutex to be acquired
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Lock the mutex like
\fBmutex_lock\fR, and return 0 if the mutex has been acquired or sleep until the mutex becomes available\&. If a signal arrives while waiting for the lock then this function returns \-EINTR\&.
.PP
This function is similar to (but not equivalent to)
\fBdown_interruptible\fR\&.
